 Name=""
><Comment>
Previous revision status was NotImplementable</Comment>
The balise is a transmission device that can send telegrams to the on-board sub-system.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.2.2"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl="3.2.0"
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.2.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
><Comment>
Previous revision status was NotImplementable</Comment>
The balise is based on the existing Eurobalise specifications. These documents are included in the frame of the ERTMS/ETCS specifications.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.2.3"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The balises provides the up-link, i. e. the possibility to send messages from trackside to the on-board sub-system.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.2.4"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The balises can provide fixed messages or, when connected to a lineside electronic unit, messages that can be changed.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.2.5"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The balises will be organised in groups, each balise transmitting a telegram and the combination of all telegrams defining the message sent by the balise group.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.3"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Lineside electronic unit<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.3.1"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The lineside electronic units are electronic devices, that generate telegrams to be sent by balises, on basis of information received from external trackside systems.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Trackside radio communication network (GSM-R)<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.1"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The GSM-R radio communication network is used for the bi-directional exchange of messages between on-board sub-systems and RBC or radio infill units.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.2"
 type="DELETED"
 scope="TRACK"
