Intentionally deleted</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.5"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>RBC<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.5.1"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The RBC is a computer-based system that elaborates messages to be sent to the train on basis of information received from external trackside systems and on basis of information exchanged with the on-board sub-systems.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.5.2"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The main objective of these messages is to provide movement authorities to allow the safe movement of trains on the Railway infrastructure area under the responsibility of the RBC.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.5.3"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The interoperability requirements for the RBC are mainly related to the data exchange between the RBC and the on-board sub-system.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.6"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU_AND_TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Euroloop<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.6.1"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The Euroloop subsystem operates on Level 1 lines, providing signalling information in advance as regard to the next main signal in the train running direction.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.6.2"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="OBU_AND_TRACK"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The Euroloop subsystem is composed of an on-board functionality and by one or more trackside parts.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.7"
