 scope="TRACK"
 bl="3.2.0"
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The RADIO INFILL subsystem operates on Level 1 lines, providing signalling information in advance as regard to the next main signal in the train running direction.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.7.2"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl="3.2.0"
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The RADIO INFILL subsystem is composed of an on-board functionality and by one or more trackside parts (named RADIO INFILL Unit).</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.8"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl="3.2.0"
 optional="FALSE"
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.2.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
><Comment>
Previous revision status was </Comment>
KMC<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.8.1"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="TRACK"
 bl="3.2.0"
 optional="FALSE"
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.2.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
><Comment>
Previous revision status was </Comment>
The role of the KMC is to manage the cryptographic keys, which are used to secure the EURORADIO communications between the ERTMS/ETCS entities (ERTMS/ETCS on-board equipments, RBCs and RIUs).</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>On-board sub-system<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.1"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Depending of the application level (see further sections), the on-board sub-system can be composed of:
	a) the ERTMS/ETCS on-board equipment;
	b) the on-board part of the GSM-R radio system;</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.2"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>ERTMS/ETCS on-board equipment<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.2.1"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The ERTMS/ETCS on-board equipment is a computer-based system that supervises the movement of the train to which it belongs, on basis of information exchanged with the trackside sub-system.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.2.2"
 type="NOTE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl="3.2.0"
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The interoperability requirements for the ERTMS/ETCS on-board equipment are related to the functionality and the data exchange between the trackside sub-systems and the on-board sub-system and to the functional data exchange between the onboard sub-system and:
	a) the driver;
	b) the train;
	c) the onboard part of the existing national train control system(s).</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.3"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Onboard radio communication system (GSM-R)<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.3.1"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The GSM-R on-board radio system is used for the bi-directional exchange of messages between on-board sub-system and RBC or radio infill unit.</Paragraph><Paragraph
